data.enText: a place where water with minerals in it, which is considered to be good for your health, comes up naturally out of the ground; the name given to a town that has such a place and where there are, or were, places where people could drink the water
a place where people can relax and improve their health, with, for example, a swimming pool

data.chText: 内设桑拿浴室、土耳其浴室和健身房的第一流的休闲健身中心
data.enText: a superb health spa which includes sauna, Turkish bath and fitness rooms

tr: a place of business with equipment and facilities for exercising and improving physical fitness
a fashionable hotel usually in a resort area
a health resort near a spring or at the seaside

value.def: A spa is a place where water with minerals in it comes out of the ground. People drink the water or go in it in order to improve their health.

example.ex: ...Fiuggi, a spa town famous for its water.
example.tran: 菲乌吉——一个以水质绝佳而闻名的温泉疗养城市

value.tran: 温泉疗养地;矿泉疗养地

value.def: A health spa is a kind of hotel where people go to do exercise and have special treatments in order to improve their health.
value.tran: 温泉疗养院;温泉疗养中心

trans: 健身庄，休闲健身中心(提供特定饮食、身体锻炼等短期休养服务)
